  }
  m_iOrder 5
 }
 E6_Negotiation {
  coords 3472.466 82.781 7140.113
  m_sTitle "NEGOTIATION"
  m_sTextData "<h2>Negotiation</h2>"\
  "Individual fighters may consider surrender if they see no other way to survive."\
  "Negotiating a surrender may become critical if a continued fight is looking too costly and personal survival is under serious danger."\
  "Even beyond that, it may be possible to secure some advantages."\
  ""\
  "<b>Some examples:</b>"\
  "- You could demand the enemy accepts your surrender or lets you leave unharmed."\
  "- You could buy time by pretending to negotiate a surrender."\
  "- If the enemy is not interested in accepting your surrender, you could say you have some information, or as the hostage guards, threaten to harm to the hostage."\
  "- Demand that the enemy lets a 1-2 other guys leave the compound freely while one guard remains, ready to kill the hostage if the friendlies are harmed."\
  ""\
  "You can physically surrender by pressing F1, upon which enemies can zip cuff you."
  m_aVisibleForFactions {
   "GC_SEPARATIST"
  }
  m_iOrder 6
 }
 A8_Notes {
  coords 3472.466 82.781 7140.113
  m_sTitle "Mission Notes"
  m_sTextData "- Setup Timer: 3 minutes, only affects the main US starting position"\
  "Extremists can leave the compound, but not with the hostages."\
  "- Default time is just before dawn, if desired the US commander can request something brighter from GMs during briefing."\
  "- The red rectangle is NOT an AO limit, the extremists can leave the compound."\
  "- Both factions can see an image of the sawmill compound to the right of the AO"\
  ""\
  "End conditions:"\
  "Upon US extraction and rescue/death of both hostages, the mission ends."\
  "Alternatively, the mission can also end at 75% US casualties."\
  "When the game ends, messages about the outcome for all parties are shown."
  m_bShowForAnyFaction 1
  m_iOrder 8
 }
}